verblex: 1. To be in or experience an unpleasant feeling in your body because you are ill or have been hurt; (be) in pain.
2. To feel a series of strong beats or dull pains in your body. English = throb.
nomlex: 1. An unpleasant feeling you have in your body because you are ill or have been hurt. English = pain.
2. A series of strong beats or dull pains in your body. English = throb.
